commit.message:
Merge pull request #21 from bryant1410/master

Fix broken headings in Markdown files (thanks a lot!)
updated .travis.yml so that installing dependencies works.
added a whitespace while tracking down a weird travis bug
* removed usage of c++11 features to make crusty old compilers happy
* outputting empty son-array, if the requested channel cannot be generated (because there are not enough channels). This is done, so that client-side javascript code does not break.
* re-build examples. note that test1 only outputs the left channel, because the input file is mono

changed the way we're looping over the samples. We're now looking only once at each input sample. we're not seeking in the input file. This is required for reading from stdin to work. A small drawback is, that we have to collect all output values in a vector before output.
* install_dependencies no longer installs dependencies twice on OS X
* enabled multi os builds on travis
* moved info about install_dependencies to right section
* updated readme for info about make install_dependencies
* added (commented out) multi os config to travis config
